   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> can be determined using the method of next-generation matrix (
 <xref rid="bib8" ref-type="bibr">Diekmann &amp; Heesterbeek, 2000</xref>). The basic reproduction number is the eigen-value of largest magnitude of the next generation matrix, that is, the number of all new infectious types in the next generation. 
